The new primate fossils occur in the Solimoes Formation at Patos, along the upper Acre River (10° 55' 55" S, 69° 550' 20" W) in a riverbank cut approximately 38 km upriver from the towns of Assis (on the Brazilian side) and Inapari (on the Peruvian side) (Fig. 1). The outcrop is visible only in the low-water season and consists of an intraformational conglomerate with clasts of clay and silt. It is part of a large paleochannel
This is a very large area, and needs to be split up. See Cozzuol 2006.
